Write a c program to sort an array of integers in ascending order and display the sorted array and number of passes performed for sorting.

import java.util.Scanner;
class FloydTriangle
{ 
public static void main(Stringargs[]) 
{ 
int n,num=1,c,d;
Scannerin=newScanner(System.in);
System.out.println("Enter the number of rows of Floyd's triangle to display"); 
n=in.nextInt();
System.out.println("Floyd's triangle:");
for(c=1;c<=n;c++) 
{ 
for(d=1;d<=c;d++)
{ 
System.out.print(num+""); num++; 
} 
System.out.println();
}
}
}


